MALIN HEAD COAST GUARD STATION Q
SEA AREA FORECAST UNTIL 0600 MONDAY 03 FEBRUARY 2014
ISSUED AT 0600 SUNDAY 02 FEBRUARY 2014
1. GALE WARNING: IN OPERATION SMALL CRAFT WARNING: IN OPERATION
2. METEOROLOGICAL SITUATION AT 0500: A STRONG SOUTHWESTERLY AIRFLOW OVER
IRELAND WILL BACK SOUTH TO SOUTHWEST TODAY AS A DEPRESSION TO THE NORTHWEST
OF SCOTLAND MOVES AWAY NORTHEASTWARDS AND CONTINUES TO FILL. A VERY STRONG
SOUTH TO SOUTHEAST AIRFLOW WILL DEVELOP LATER A TODAY AND TONIGHT AS COLD
FRONT APPROACHES FROM THE ATLANTIC.
3. FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM FAIR HEAD TO CARNSORE POINT TO MIZEN HEAD AND
FOR THE IRISH SEA :
WIND: SOUTHWESTERLY FORCE 6 OR 7 AND GUSTY DECREASING SOUTHWEST TO SOUTH
FORCE 5 OR 6 TODAY BUT INCREASING SOUTH TO SOUTHEAST FORCE 7 TO GALE FORCE
8 BY MIDNIGHT AND FURTHER INCREASING GALE FORCE 8 TO STRONG GALE FORCE 9
OVERNIGHT POSSIBLY TOUCHING STORM FORCE IN THE SOUTHWEST LATER.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM MIZEN HEAD TO LOOP HEAD TO SLYNE HEAD:
WIND: SOUTHWESTERLY FORCE 5 OR 6 AND GUSTY GRADUALLY BACKING SOUTHERLY
TODAY AND INCREASING FORCE 7 TO GALE FORCE 8 BY EVENING FURTHER INCREASING
SOUTH TO SOUTHEAST GALE FORCE 8 TO STRONG GALE FORCE 9 TONIGHT.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM SLYNE HEAD TO MALIN HEAD TO FAIR HEAD :
WIND: SOUTHWESTERLY FORCE 7 TO GALE FORCE 8 DECREASING SOUTHWESTERLY
FORCE 6 OR 7 LATER TODAY BUT INCREASING SOUTH TO SOUTHEAST GALE FORCE 8
TO STRONG GALE FORCE 9 TONIGHT.
WEATHER FOR ALL SEA AREAS: SCATTERED SHOWERS WITH PATCHY RAIN AND DRIZZLE
DEVELOPING TODAY MAINLY IN THE SOUTH AND WEST.
VISIBILITY FOR ALL SEA AREAS: MODERATE TO POOR AT TIMES IN RAIN OR SHOWERS.
OTHERWISE GOOD.
3A. WARNING OF HEAVY SWELL: ON SOUTHERN WESTERN AND NORTHERN COASTS
4. OUTLOOK FOR A FURTHER 24 HOURS UNTIL 0600 TUESDAY 04 FEBRUARY 2014:
SOUTH TO SOUTHEAST GALES OR STRONG GALES POSSIBLY REACHING STORM FORCE IN
THE SOUTH AND SOUTHWEST GRADUALLY VEERING SOUTHWESTERLY AND LATER DECREASING
FRESH TO STRONG. RAIN FOR A TIME ON MONDAY MORNING CLEARING TO SHOWERS.
